column3: TISSUE DESCRIPTION : Left upper lobe lung ( 100 grams , 15.0 X 7.5 X 5.0 cm ) , superior mediastinal ( left lower paratracheal ) , aortic ( subaortic , para-aortic ) , inferior mediastinal ( subcarinal , left pulmonary ligament ) and N1 ( interlobar , lobar ) lymph nodes .

The tumor is 4.5 cm from the bronchial margin .

Lymph nodes , superior and inferior mediastinal , aortic , Nl , excision : Multiple ( 2 left lower paratracheal , 6 subaortic , 1 para-aortic , 14 subcarinal , 2 left pulmonary artery , 1 interlobar , 1 lobar ) lymph nodes are negative for tumor .
